verbose_text: The general consensus is that basal autophagy can protect plaque cells against oxidative stress by degrading damaged intracellular material and promoting cell survival, and excessive stimulation of autophagy may cause autophagic cell death, leading to reduced synthesis of collagen, thinning of the fibrous cap, plaque destabilization, lesional thrombosis, and acute clinical events.
evidence: autophagy may cause autophagic cell death
